<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>

 <%= stylesheet_link_tag    'application', media: 'all', 'data-turbolinks-track' => true %>
 <%= javascript_include_tag 'application', 'data-turbolinks-track' => true %>
 <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
</head>


  <nav class="navbar navbar-default navbar-inverse navbar-fixed-top">
    <div class="container-fluid row">

      <div class="col-sm-4"><strong> Stripe Fees </strong></div>
      <% if (@user != nil) %>
        <div class="col-sm-4">Welcome <a href="/profile" class="text-muted"><%= @user.username %></a>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-4">
        <%= form_tag('/log_out', method: :delete) do %>
        <%= submit_tag "Log-Out " %>
        <% end %>
        </div>
      <% else %>
        <div class="col-sm-4 pull-right">Welcome <%= "Guest" %>
        </div>
        <% end %>


    </div>
  </nav>

<body class="bg-primary">
  <h3>Please sign in</h3>
<div class="bg-info text-info">
  <% if (@user != nil) %>
        <%= "Hi " + @user.username + ". Let's go back to your " %><a href="/profile" class="text-muted"> profile</a>
      <% else %>



      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-8">
        <%= form_tag('/log_in', method: :post) do %>
          <%= label_tag :username %>
          <%= text_field_tag :username %>
          <%= label_tag :password %>
          <%= password_field_tag :password %>
          <%= submit_tag "Submit" %>
        <% end %>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-4">
        <%= form_tag('/new', method: :get) do %>
        <%= submit_tag "New users click here " %>
        <% end %>
      <% end %>
        </div>
      </div>

<article>Stripe will show your fees for an individual transaction, but what it doesn't seem to do is show you your fees over a given date range. This application aims to solve that problem. </article>

</body>
</html>
